    "title" : "Is there a way in Spring RestClient to do retries similar to WebClient filter?",
    "body" : "<p>In the implementation of RestClient there is no filter method, unlike WebClient which allows for retry. I'm also using the RestClient in the context of HTTP interface, and I don't want to create a service that has the interface just to add the retry. Is there a way to add a retry?</p>\n<p>The underlying HTTP client of my REST client is Reactor.</p>\n",
