    "answer_id" : 79645323,
    "question_id" : 79644967,
    "body" : "<p>The class <code>RetryableClientHttpRequestInterceptor</code> from this library seems to do what you want:<br />\n<a href=\"https://github.com/making/retryable-client-http-request-interceptor\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/making/retryable-client-http-request-interceptor</a></p>\n<p>Usage, as written in the README:</p>\n<pre><code>// Spring 6.1+ / Spring Boot 3.2+\nprivate final RestClient restClient;\n\npublic MyClient(RestClient.Builder builder){\n    this.restClient = builder\n        .baseUrl(&quot;http://example.com&quot;)\n        .requestInterceptor(new RetryableClientHttpRequestInterceptor(new FixedBackOff(100, 2)))\n        .build();\n}\n</code></pre>\n",
